<h1>Secure Patient-Controlled Digital Health Record System</h1>

<p>
This project aims to solve the problem of scattered and inaccessible medical records by creating a
secure digital health record platform where patients can store and manage their medical reports
in one place.
</p>

<h2>Project Overview</h2>
<p>
The system allows patients to upload and store medical reports securely in encrypted cloud storage.
Patients have full control over their data and can grant temporary access to authorized doctors
using a smart permission system.
</p>

<h2>Security Features</h2>
<p>
All reports are encrypted using AES encryption and a SHA-256 hash is generated for each file to
detect tampering. Data transfer between users and the server is protected using TLS secure communication.
</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>
The platform also supports QR-based health cards and OTP verification so doctors can access patient
records even if the patient does not have a smartphone.
</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>
<ul>
<li>Secure encrypted storage of medical records</li>
<li>Patient-controlled access to doctors</li>
<li>Smart permission system with time-limited access</li>
<li>Hash-based verification to prevent report tampering</li>
<li>QR-based emergency access to health records</li>
</ul>

